Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_dump_picture(25.10)                                gui_dump_picture(25.10)

Name
       gui_dump_picture  -  Saves a snapshot of the layout or specified window
       with the specified name in the current directory

Syntax
       gui_dump_picture

       [-help]

       <filename>

        [-format {BMP GIF JPG JPEG PNG PBM PGM PPM XBM XPM}]

       [-honor_umask]

       [-width <integer_value> -height <integer_value>]

       [-window <string>]

       Saves a snapshot of the layout or specified window with  the  specified
       name  in the current directory. You can specify the size as well as the
       format in which you want to save the snapshot. The command also  prints
       out overlay maps with legends.

       You can use this command at any stage of the design flow.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each gui_dump_picture parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man gui_dump_picture

       <filename>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  picture file as a string. You can
              specify the file extension as well.

              Note: The file extension you specify does not control the format
              of the picture. The picture file is dumped in the PNG format  by
              default  or  the format you explicitly specify with -format. For
              example, the following command saves the testShot  picture  file
              in the PNG format:

              innovus 34> gui_dump_picture testShot.gif

              <current_directory>@file testShot.gif

              testShot.gif:  PNG  image data, 540 x 688, 8-bit/color RGB, non-
              interlaced

       -format {BMP GIF JPG JPEG PNG PBM PGM PPM XBM XPM}
              Specifies the format of the picture file.

              Default: PNG

       -height <integer_value>
              Specifies the height of the picture as an integral value.

              Note: The -width parameter is required when  -height  is  speci-
              fied.

              Min: 100

              Max: 20000

       -honor_umask
              Honors the umask settings while saving the picture. If you spec-
              ify  this  option, the permission of the saved picture file will
              be set by subtracting the umask value from the  full  permission
              value.

              For  example,  if  the full permission setting of a file is 0666
              and the umask setting is 0022, the tool saves the  picture  file
              with the permission setting of 0666 - 0022, that is 0644.

       -width <integer_value>
              Specifies the width of the picture as an integral value.

              Note:  The  -height  parameter is required when -width is speci-
              fied.

              Min: 100

              Max: 20000

       -window <string>
              Specifies the ID of the window that you want to  dump.  You  can
              use the following IDs:

              * For Layout Viewer: designview.win

              * For Cell Viewer: .uiCellView.win

              If  -window is not specified, the layout window is dumped out by
              default.

Examples
              * The following command captures the layout window and saves  it
                in the default PNG format with the name <test2> and the dimen-
                sions 1000 x 1000 in the current directory:

                gui_dump_picture test2 -width 1000 height 1000

              * The  following command captures the layout window and saves it
                in the GIF format with the name <test1.gif> in the current di-
                rectory:

                gui_dump_picture -format GIF test1.gif

              * The following command captures the layout  viewer  window  and
                saves  it in PNG format with the name testShot.png in the cur-
                rent directory:

                gui_dump_picture testShot.png -window designview.win

                Note: You must have the layout viewer open.

              * The following command captures the view  in  the  cell  viewer
                window  and  saves it in PNG format with the name testCell.png
                in the current directory:

                gui_dump_picture testCell.png -window .uiCellView.win

